New Records: Shohei Ohtani recorded his 47th home run and 48th stolen base of the season in the Dodgers' comeback 10-8 win over the Cubs.
Key Match Events: The Dodgers scored two runs in the bottom of the ninth inning to win the game.
Tommy Edman set his season high with 4 runs batted in and his career high with 4 RBIs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game had a total of 18 runs, exceeding the over/under of 9.
